article.headline: San Diego St. 72, CS Northridge 56
article.story: SAN DIEGO -- Kyle Spain scored 22 points and San Diego State beat Cal State Northridge 72-56 Monday. The Matadors (3-7) trailed by 10 points after halftime before the Aztecs went on a 12-3 run, capped by a 3 from Spain that extended the lead to 60-41 midway through the second half. D.J. Gay added 20 points for San Diego State (9-3). Deon Tresvant led Northridge with 18 points, and Josh Jenkins had 11 points. Cal State Northridge trailed most of the game, holding its last lead at 20-18 with 6:20 left in the first half. It trailed 39-27 at halftime.
